WEBVTT

00:00.671 --> 00:02.079
Previously on...

00:02.103 --> 00:04.760
George paid for what he did
to your father.

00:04.784 --> 00:06.053
Bree confessed...

00:06.077 --> 00:08.615
Did you give Zach money
to go to Utah?

00:08.639 --> 00:12.119
Susan betrayed Mike...
What kind of friend is he?

00:12.143 --> 00:14.596
The real good kind.
Andrew pushed the boundaries...

00:14.620 --> 00:16.993
Zach's come home.
Is there anything I can do?

00:17.017 --> 00:19.466
Paul put his foot down...
You can leave us alone.

00:19.490 --> 00:21.198
So when do I tell people
you'll be back?

00:21.222 --> 00:22.669
Couple, maybe three days.

00:22.693 --> 00:28.303
And a stranger
finally caught up with Caleb.

00:30.561 --> 00:32.539
Kisses are such simple things,

00:32.563 --> 00:35.112
we hardly notice them.

00:35.136 --> 00:37.384
But if we paid more attention,

00:37.408 --> 00:41.318
we'd see that each kiss
conveys a meaning all its own.

00:41.342 --> 00:47.194
For example, some can say,
"I'm so happy to see you."

00:47.218 --> 00:51.798
Or, "I didn't realize
you'dbe here."

00:51.822 --> 00:53.230
Bye.

00:53.254 --> 00:57.734
Or, "honey,
it's time to stop drinking."

00:57.758 --> 01:01.568
The trick is in knowing
how to tell the difference.

01:01.592 --> 01:05.072
So I finally said,
if I'm head cheerleader,

01:05.096 --> 01:07.214
then nobody wears panties.

01:07.238 --> 01:08.238
Yeah!

01:10.101 --> 01:12.079
I just want you to know
as a former member

01:12.103 --> 01:14.626
of my high school marching band,
I would've appreciated that.

01:14.650 --> 01:18.225
Wait a second, you were a band
geek? Oh, I don't believe it.

01:18.249 --> 01:21.358
What did you play? He
played the tuba. I have pictures.

01:21.382 --> 01:23.360
The tuba, huh?

01:23.384 --> 01:25.371
Yeah, go ahead, come on, come
on, get your licks in, go ahead.

01:25.395 --> 01:27.364
No, no, not at all.
As a matter of fact,

01:27.388 --> 01:29.666
all of my secret crushes
were on the band geeks.

01:29.690 --> 01:31.198
Come on,
I know you cheerleader types.

01:31.222 --> 01:32.799
You wouldn't have said "boo"
to guys like me.

01:32.823 --> 01:35.250
No, you were more interested
in the guys like... like this.

01:35.274 --> 01:38.305
Now, I take it
you didn't play the tuba.

01:38.329 --> 01:40.777
No, I didn't.

01:40.801 --> 01:44.651
All I know is, I was a lonely,
insecure tuba player.

01:44.675 --> 01:47.114
Girls like Gabrielle would just
rip my heart out.

01:47.138 --> 01:48.285
Aw.

01:48.309 --> 01:50.187
I didn't even had my first kiss
until I was 18.

01:50.211 --> 01:52.289
18? Pathetic, I know.

01:52.313 --> 01:54.291
Poor baby.
I would've kissed you.

01:54.315 --> 01:55.822
No, you wouldn't have.
Yes, I would have.

01:55.846 --> 01:59.266
No, you wouldn't have.
And it's okay, Gaby.

01:59.290 --> 02:00.527
Those scars healed
a long time ago.

02:00.551 --> 02:03.270
Oh, for god sakes, come here.

02:03.294 --> 02:06.141
Now on behalf of all
the cheerleaders in the world,

02:06.165 --> 02:07.674
forgive us.

02:07.698 --> 02:11.138
Oh, yeah! Whoo!

02:11.162 --> 02:17.784
Yes, kisses mean different
things to different people.

02:17.808 --> 02:19.286
Ultimately, the meaning depends

02:19.310 --> 02:21.288
on the one who does
the kissing...

02:21.312 --> 02:23.420
Wowie.

02:23.444 --> 02:26.393
Cheers.

02:26.417 --> 02:34.417
And the who sees it happen.

02:41.492 --> 02:45.842
After every party
comes the time for cleaning.

02:45.866 --> 02:48.845
We attend to the champagne
that was spilled,

02:48.869 --> 02:53.220
the knickknacks that got broken,

02:53.244 --> 02:58.655
the food that went uneaten.

02:58.679 --> 03:01.228
Oh, here, let me take that.

03:01.252 --> 03:05.192
And whatever other messes
need cleaning up.

03:05.216 --> 03:08.535
So, uh, Gaby...

03:08.559 --> 03:11.298
You know that thing
you and Tom did tonight?

03:11.322 --> 03:12.439
The... the kiss?

03:12.463 --> 03:15.442
Was that hysterical?
The look on Tom's face!

03:15.466 --> 03:17.966
Yeah.

03:24.535 --> 03:29.856
I know this sounds silly, but...

03:29.880 --> 03:31.918
It kind of bugged me.

03:31.942 --> 03:34.261
You're not serious.

03:34.285 --> 03:35.762
Yeah, I am.

03:35.786 --> 03:38.295
I don't... I don't want to make

03:38.319 --> 03:39.796
a big deal out of it, but, uh,

03:39.820 --> 03:43.970
could you maybe
not do that again?

03:43.994 --> 03:46.433
Okay.

03:46.457 --> 03:48.605
Thanks.

03:48.629 --> 03:50.607
Okay.

03:50.631 --> 03:52.609
Hey, what happened to
the applewhites?

03:52.633 --> 03:54.750
I thought you were
gonna invite them.

03:54.774 --> 03:57.244
I did. Betty never r.S.V.P.'D.

03:57.268 --> 03:58.645
What do you guys think
about the applewhites?

03:58.669 --> 04:00.647
I like 'em, very nice. Very...

04:00.671 --> 04:01.948
Interesting.

04:01.972 --> 04:03.720
Right, interesting.

04:03.744 --> 04:05.357
Hmm, they weird me out, too.

04:05.381 --> 04:07.324
Well, that's not
what we're saying.

04:07.348 --> 04:09.496
Not exactly, anyway.

04:09.520 --> 04:11.828
You know,
we were just having fun,

04:11.852 --> 04:13.360
entertaining the crowd.

04:13.384 --> 04:14.801
Oh, sure, but...

04:14.825 --> 04:18.233
But maybe next time
you could try juggling instead.

04:18.257 --> 04:19.988
What's going on? Nothing.

04:22.363 --> 04:25.372
Really?
I sense a little tension.

04:25.396 --> 04:26.636
No, no tension.

04:31.271 --> 04:32.379
What?

04:32.403 --> 04:33.850
You make it sound like...

04:33.874 --> 04:35.331
I was making a pass
at your husband.

04:35.355 --> 04:38.325
And that's just
a little bit insulting.

04:38.349 --> 04:42.028
I just said it bugged me.

04:42.052 --> 04:43.330
Why is that a problem?

04:43.354 --> 04:45.701
Is this about that kiss?
What kiss?

04:45.725 --> 04:47.994
Oh, you were in the living room.

04:48.018 --> 04:50.837
Gaby planted a big, wet kiss
on Tom... as a joke.

04:50.861 --> 04:51.838
It was hilarious.

04:51.862 --> 04:53.500
You see?

04:53.524 --> 04:56.277
Yeah, but to be fair
to Lynette, you are an ex-model.

04:56.301 --> 04:58.975
And surely it must have
dawned on you that some women

04:58.999 --> 05:02.609
might prefer it if you didn't kiss
their husbands. That's all I'm saying.

05:02.633 --> 05:04.911
Oh, you guys, we're all friends.

05:04.935 --> 05:06.983
This isn't something
to get worked up over.

05:07.007 --> 05:08.655
I'm not worked up.

05:08.679 --> 05:10.439
Me neither.

05:12.383 --> 05:15.370
Hey, everyone, did you see what
Kathy Lewis was wearing tonight?

05:15.394 --> 05:18.465
And whoever told her
that she could get away

05:18.489 --> 05:20.527
with those vertical stripes
should be shot.

05:20.551 --> 05:22.451
Oh. Bye, sweetie.

05:37.067 --> 05:39.045
Uh...

05:39.069 --> 05:41.439
Oh!

05:49.480 --> 05:51.458
Zach is back!

05:51.482 --> 05:53.460
Yeah, yeah, I know.

05:53.484 --> 05:55.031
You do?

05:55.055 --> 05:57.033
Yeah, he's been back
for a couple of days now.

05:57.057 --> 06:00.437
Well, that's great,
isn't it? Yeah.

06:00.461 --> 06:02.439
I thought
you'd be happy about it.

06:02.463 --> 06:04.480
I thought
that's what you wanted.

06:04.504 --> 06:05.972
I was hoping

06:05.996 --> 06:07.974
that I'd slowly establish
a relationship with Zach

06:07.998 --> 06:09.976
and then when we were
comfortable,

06:10.000 --> 06:11.918
I'd tell him I was his real dad.
But now Paul's back.

06:11.942 --> 06:13.620
And he doesn't want you
anywhere near him.

06:13.644 --> 06:15.627
He's threatened
to tell the police

06:15.651 --> 06:17.624
everything that happened
in the desert...

06:17.648 --> 06:19.786
That I held a gun to his head.

06:19.810 --> 06:21.788
Well, it's your word
against his.

06:21.812 --> 06:23.660
But he doesn't have
a record, and I do.

06:23.684 --> 06:28.134
You know, despite what I did...

06:28.158 --> 06:30.937
Sending Zach away,

06:30.961 --> 06:32.799
I want you two to connect.
I hope you know that.

06:32.823 --> 06:34.703
I do.

06:36.026 --> 06:38.805
And on the bright side,

06:38.829 --> 06:41.729
I don't have to wonder
where he is anymore.

06:46.577 --> 06:49.786
It says that you can do
a report on anything

06:49.810 --> 06:51.387
from the suggested reading list,
which includes

06:51.411 --> 06:54.461
"the old man and the sea,"
"the Pearl,"

06:54.485 --> 06:56.463
"much ado about nothing."

06:56.487 --> 06:59.095
Hmm. That sounds good.
What do you like?

06:59.119 --> 07:00.689
I don't care.

07:02.793 --> 07:04.676
Let's start with "the Pearl."

07:04.700 --> 07:07.525
It's got a sad ending, but it's
good. We'll start with that.

07:11.532 --> 07:14.511
You know,
it's not gonna be so bad.

07:14.535 --> 07:16.575
I think you're really gonna like
being homeschooled.

07:18.869 --> 07:23.550
Okay, I know this isn't
what you want.

07:23.574 --> 07:25.461
But I need to keep you
close to me

07:25.485 --> 07:26.693
just for a while.

07:26.717 --> 07:28.555
There are people
in this neighborhood

07:28.579 --> 07:30.597
who aren't thrilled
that we're back.

07:30.621 --> 07:33.700
People I don't trust.

07:33.724 --> 07:36.202
People like... Mike Delfino?

07:36.226 --> 07:38.705
Why would you say that?

07:38.729 --> 07:40.206
When you disappeared,

07:40.230 --> 07:43.910
Mrs. Tillman said that Mike
took you somewhere to kill you.

07:43.934 --> 07:47.614
That's ridiculous.
Why would Mike wanna kill me?

07:47.638 --> 07:49.598
Because you murdered Mrs. Huber?

07:51.642 --> 07:53.449
What did you say?

07:53.473 --> 07:55.560
Well, Mrs. Tillman said that
you murdered Mrs. Huber

07:55.584 --> 07:57.524
because she was
blackmailing mom.

07:57.548 --> 07:58.785
And you believed her?

07:58.809 --> 08:00.487
No, not exactly.

08:00.511 --> 08:02.859
I mean, why? Should I?

08:02.883 --> 08:08.194
Zach, you know me
better than anyone.

08:08.218 --> 08:10.867
Do you honestly believe

08:10.891 --> 08:12.839
that I am capable of murder?

08:12.863 --> 08:15.171
No.

08:15.195 --> 08:16.695
All right, then.

08:18.569 --> 08:21.508
Of course...

08:21.532 --> 08:25.112
I didn't think mom was capable
of suicide, either.

08:27.037 --> 08:28.515
On second thought,

08:28.539 --> 08:32.188
why don't we start with
"much ado about nothing"?

08:32.212 --> 08:36.491
I think we could use
a few laughs around here.

08:36.515 --> 08:38.625
Yeah, man...

08:38.649 --> 08:41.727
Yeah, he sure is. I just...

08:41.751 --> 08:44.152
Probably. Yeah.

08:56.106 --> 08:57.083
Hey.

08:57.107 --> 08:59.586
Get over here.

08:59.610 --> 09:02.248
Now.

09:02.272 --> 09:04.551
Somebody's angry.

09:04.575 --> 09:06.593
Did one of your soufflés fall?

09:06.617 --> 09:09.155
I saw what you did
with your friend.

09:09.179 --> 09:11.628
Oh, and you didn't turn into
a pillar of salt. Good for you.

09:11.652 --> 09:13.129
This is not a joke, Andrew.

09:13.153 --> 09:15.201
What if the neighbors
had seen you?

09:15.225 --> 09:16.963
Well, I'd hope they'd think
that I'd landed a hottie.

09:16.987 --> 09:18.965
I may not be able to control

09:18.989 --> 09:20.967
what you do outside
of this home,

09:20.991 --> 09:22.969
but while
you are under this roof,

09:22.993 --> 09:24.941
you will not mock my values.

09:24.965 --> 09:27.113
If you so much
as smile at that boy,

09:27.137 --> 09:29.646
so help me, I will ship you off
to camp hennessey

09:29.670 --> 09:31.648
and I will not pick you up
again until you are 18.

09:31.672 --> 09:33.672
Do I make myself clear?

09:37.978 --> 09:39.726
Aren't you forgetting something?

09:39.750 --> 09:42.010
I know you like to knock
a few back before bedtime.

09:43.754 --> 09:46.032
Go on, take it. It's okay.

09:46.056 --> 09:49.135
We both know
that of the two of us,

09:49.159 --> 09:50.959
I'm the one that doesn't judge.

10:07.607 --> 10:11.688
Please. I don't wanna
stay down here.

10:11.712 --> 10:13.920
I-I know.

10:13.944 --> 10:16.623
I'm sorry, k.

10:16.647 --> 10:17.817
I'm sorry.

10:22.923 --> 10:24.906
Matthew, I think we might
have termites.

10:24.930 --> 10:26.903
You need to take
a look at those steps

10:26.927 --> 10:29.605
before one of us
breaks our neck.

10:29.629 --> 10:32.138
What's the matter?
Is your brother okay?

10:32.162 --> 10:34.310
No, he's not.
He hates it down here.

10:34.334 --> 10:37.684
He wants to be with us.
You're being cruel.

10:37.708 --> 10:39.746
If you are so concerned
about him,

10:39.770 --> 10:42.318
you should spend less time
on your computer

10:42.342 --> 10:44.320
and more time down here
keeping him company.

10:44.344 --> 10:45.822
We're bringing him up,

10:45.846 --> 10:50.256
but not until I am sure
that it's safe.

10:50.280 --> 10:53.860
♪ there's been
a load of compromising ♪

10:53.884 --> 10:58.294
♪ On the road to my horizon ♪

11:05.836 --> 11:06.813
Hey, you!

11:06.837 --> 11:09.976
♪ Like a rhinestone cowboy ♪

11:12.372 --> 11:13.649
Yeah?

11:13.673 --> 11:15.752
What's the deal?

11:15.776 --> 11:17.724
You've been parked on our street
for two hours.

11:17.748 --> 11:19.986
Oh, I'm doing
a property appraisal.

11:20.010 --> 11:21.988
Some neighbors of yours
are thinking about moving.

11:22.012 --> 11:23.659
The applewhites?

11:23.683 --> 11:25.992
I'm not really allowed to say.

11:26.016 --> 11:29.696
I sold them that house.
You know, this is my turf!

11:29.720 --> 11:31.197
Who do you work for?

11:31.221 --> 11:32.438
Geist realty?

11:32.462 --> 11:34.670
Ah, westside properties.

11:34.694 --> 11:36.803
Yeah, well, whoever it is,
you go back

11:36.827 --> 11:38.805
and you tell your bosses
that nobody, and I mean, nobody,

11:38.829 --> 11:40.807
buys or sells properties
in this neighborhood

11:40.831 --> 11:43.149
without going through
Edie britt, you got that?

11:43.173 --> 11:45.852
Look, lady, I just go
where I'm told.

11:45.876 --> 11:47.854
You look, you cross me,

11:47.878 --> 11:52.859
and I will be
your worst nightmare.

11:52.883 --> 11:55.723
I'm a dangerous woman.
You don't wanna mess with me.

11:57.818 --> 11:59.288
You got it.

12:12.362 --> 12:13.780
Ms. Mayer?

12:13.804 --> 12:15.782
Zach. May I talk to you?

12:15.806 --> 12:17.413
I have some things
that I need to say.

12:17.437 --> 12:19.245
Okay.

12:19.269 --> 12:22.088
I-I know that I did
a lot of bad stuff...

12:22.112 --> 12:24.826
Stuff that I'm not gonna
be able to take back.

12:24.850 --> 12:26.753
Ms. Mayer,
I'm... I'm really sorry.

12:26.777 --> 12:28.755
But when I was living
on the streets, you know,

12:28.779 --> 12:31.758
I had a lot of time to...
To just sit and think to myself

12:31.782 --> 12:33.499
and clear my head and...

12:33.523 --> 12:36.037
I've grown up, you know?
I don't want you to worry.

12:36.061 --> 12:38.464
I'm not gonna be
bothering you anymore.

12:38.488 --> 12:40.888
Either of you.

12:42.993 --> 12:46.242
Well, thanks.
We appreciate that.

12:46.266 --> 12:50.877
Please don't tell my dad
that I talked to you.

12:50.901 --> 12:53.019
He's just... he's been really...

12:53.043 --> 12:54.913
Intense lately.

13:00.450 --> 13:02.428
Well, what do you think?

13:02.452 --> 13:04.430
He seems different.

13:04.454 --> 13:06.432
I believe him.

13:06.456 --> 13:08.434
Yeah, I can't believe
I'm about to say this,

13:08.458 --> 13:10.466
but I feel sorry for him.

13:10.490 --> 13:12.468
It's like he's so fragile.

13:12.492 --> 13:15.902
I know, and he's locked in that
house with Mr. Creepy 24/7.

13:15.926 --> 13:17.773
Did you know that he's
homeschooling Zach now?

13:17.797 --> 13:20.346
I think he should
spend some time

13:20.370 --> 13:22.870
with a decent role model,
don't you?

13:29.279 --> 13:31.017
Hi!

13:31.041 --> 13:32.188
Hey, you're out early.

13:32.212 --> 13:34.190
Oh, I just wanted to pick up

13:34.214 --> 13:36.823
some fresh croissants
for breakfast.

13:36.847 --> 13:39.225
Oh, cool. Listen,
I just wanted you to know

13:39.249 --> 13:41.928
I appreciated you
backing me up last night,

13:41.952 --> 13:44.170
you know, with the kiss thing.

13:44.194 --> 13:46.908
To be honest, I don't think
I would've liked it, either.

13:46.932 --> 13:49.505
Yeah, but I probably
should've just gone with it.

13:49.529 --> 13:51.938
Gaby was just being Gaby...
Having fun.

13:51.962 --> 13:55.289
No, I wouldn't be so hard
on yourself, given her history.

13:55.313 --> 13:57.283
What do you mean?

13:57.307 --> 14:00.446
You know, the affair.
Gaby had an affair?

14:00.470 --> 14:02.048
You didn't know? No!

14:02.072 --> 14:04.550
I thought everybody knew.

14:04.574 --> 14:07.053
Oh, I feel awful.

14:07.077 --> 14:08.824
Oh, ida Greenberg's behind you.

14:08.848 --> 14:11.827
Ida, just a second.

14:11.851 --> 14:15.231
I am stunned. Who was it with?

14:15.255 --> 14:17.133
I shouldn't have said anything.

14:17.157 --> 14:19.257
Bree, come on, just tell me.

14:20.891 --> 14:23.191
Her gardener.

14:25.996 --> 14:27.843
Oh, you're kidding!

14:27.867 --> 14:30.176
No, no, not him.
Helen rowland's son, John.

14:30.200 --> 14:31.847
The teenager?

14:33.873 --> 14:36.322
Ida, wait, or go around!

14:36.346 --> 14:38.324
Does Gaby know that you know?

14:38.348 --> 14:39.625
Absolutely not.

14:39.649 --> 14:41.627
I think the best thing to do

14:41.651 --> 14:44.481
is just smile and pretend
you don't know anything.

14:56.566 --> 14:58.166
Huh.

15:00.070 --> 15:01.908
Hi.

15:01.932 --> 15:03.002
Oh, sorry!

15:05.005 --> 15:06.012
Are you okay?

15:06.036 --> 15:08.985
Yeah.

15:09.009 --> 15:11.887
I'm all right. What's up?

15:11.911 --> 15:14.611
We have an idea how to bring
you and Zach together.

15:16.046 --> 15:18.164
Bowling. Bowling?

15:18.188 --> 15:20.166
Yeah, I e-mailed Zach,

15:20.190 --> 15:22.498
and he said he's gonna meet
us there. You can come, too.

15:22.522 --> 15:24.200
Does Paul know about this?

15:24.224 --> 15:28.104
No, and we're not planning
on telling him.

15:28.128 --> 15:32.108
I don't think
that's a good idea, Susan.

15:32.132 --> 15:35.246
Mike, I'm part of the reason
things got so screwed up.

15:35.270 --> 15:37.944
I just want a chance
to make things right.

15:37.968 --> 15:41.047
And you're okay with this...
Being around Zach?

15:41.071 --> 15:44.951
We talked to him. He's changed.

15:44.975 --> 15:49.675
Well, I guess
we're going bowling.

15:51.982 --> 15:53.259
Wake up, sleepyhead.

15:53.283 --> 15:56.293
I brought fresh croissants
for breakfast!

16:03.693 --> 16:06.672
Uh, hi, Mrs. Van De Kamp.

16:06.696 --> 16:09.296
I'm Justin,
Andrew's lab partner...

16:10.400 --> 16:12.478
From school.

16:12.502 --> 16:14.080
Dude, wake up.

16:14.104 --> 16:16.382
Andrew...

16:16.406 --> 16:18.746
I want you downstairs... Now.

16:29.359 --> 16:31.337
Okay, first of all, I want you
to march back upstairs

16:31.361 --> 16:34.570
and tell your friend he is
no longer welcome in this house.

16:34.594 --> 16:37.151
But we haven't even had
