Good.

35:53.422 --> 35:54.899
Hey, neighbor.

35:54.923 --> 35:57.162
Oh, hey, Carlos.

35:57.186 --> 35:58.363
Hi.

35:58.387 --> 36:01.206
I just wanted to thank you for
patching things up with Gaby.

36:01.230 --> 36:03.368
Well, sure, no problem.

36:03.392 --> 36:05.370
It's been really tough on her...

36:05.394 --> 36:08.142
Everybody finding out
about the affair.

36:08.166 --> 36:10.475
Yeah, I can imagine.

36:10.499 --> 36:12.677
I don't mind telling you,
it's, uh...

36:12.701 --> 36:14.719
It's been pretty tough on us
the past couple months.

36:14.743 --> 36:17.282
Oh, well, I'm not surprised,

36:17.306 --> 36:20.285
and I really, really hope
you can work it out.

36:20.309 --> 36:22.257
Yeah, we're trying. You know...

36:22.281 --> 36:23.888
Mm-hmm? Yeah?

36:23.912 --> 36:27.161
Gaby had
an interesting suggestion.

36:27.185 --> 36:28.162
Oh?

36:28.186 --> 36:31.296
She told me that I should go out

36:31.320 --> 36:33.298
and have an affair of my own.

36:33.322 --> 36:34.939
She thinks it's the only way

36:34.963 --> 36:36.946
I'll be able to get over
what she did to me

36:36.970 --> 36:39.244
and that it just might
help our marriage.

36:39.268 --> 36:41.646
Why are you telling me this?

36:41.670 --> 36:43.348
Uh...

36:43.372 --> 36:46.351
I guess I just, uh...

36:46.375 --> 36:49.775
Wanted to know if you had
any thoughts on the subject?

36:51.580 --> 36:53.788
I... don't.

36:53.812 --> 36:56.321
I really don't.

36:56.345 --> 37:00.845
Well, if you ever do,
let me know.

37:02.691 --> 37:04.599
By the way...

37:04.623 --> 37:05.930
Mm-hmm?

37:05.954 --> 37:09.704
That was one hell
of a kiss you gave me.

37:09.728 --> 37:13.558
You can't fake
chemistry like that.

37:46.295 --> 37:48.435
What the hell is this?

38:01.380 --> 38:03.388
Delfino?

38:03.412 --> 38:05.290
Uhh!

38:05.314 --> 38:08.524
Stay away from my son!

38:17.896 --> 38:20.274
Oh, my god!

38:28.306 --> 38:30.376
Dad!

38:33.442 --> 38:34.889
You okay? I'm fine.

38:34.913 --> 38:37.493
Aah!

39:04.513 --> 39:06.796
So I swerved
to avoid hitting his car,

39:06.820 --> 39:08.793
and I hit this parked car
instead,

39:08.817 --> 39:10.795
and that's when
the trunk popped open,

39:10.819 --> 39:14.019
and when we got out, we found
this dead body and...

39:18.427 --> 39:20.435
Are you worried now?

39:20.459 --> 39:23.107
'Cause I am.

39:23.131 --> 39:26.771
Not yet. Just be patient.
See what happens.

39:28.697 --> 39:30.375
How'd it go?

39:30.399 --> 39:32.377
Well, I told him
everything I know,

39:32.401 --> 39:34.519
which wasn't much.

39:34.543 --> 39:36.426
So are we thinking this is Paul?

39:36.450 --> 39:38.553
Well, he is our friendly
neighborhood murderer.

39:38.577 --> 39:40.555
Yeah, it seems obvious.

39:40.579 --> 39:43.458
I don't know. I saw his face
when he looked in the trunk.

39:43.482 --> 39:45.430
And he looked
just as shocked as I was.

39:45.454 --> 39:48.092
I'm thinking
it's the applewhites.

39:48.116 --> 39:49.734
I talked to the dead guy,

39:49.758 --> 39:52.597
and he said that he was doing
an appraisal on their house.

39:52.621 --> 39:54.599
Well, I got a little cheesed,

39:54.623 --> 39:56.610
so I called every realtor
in town.

39:56.634 --> 39:58.573
Nobody had even heard of him.

39:58.597 --> 40:01.546
That doesn't mean
Betty knew him.

40:01.570 --> 40:03.448
Please. Those two are fishy.

40:03.472 --> 40:06.451
They bought that house
sight unseen,

40:06.475 --> 40:09.414
and they did move in
in the middle of the night.

40:09.438 --> 40:12.617
And there were the noises.
What noises?

40:12.641 --> 40:15.760
Oh, a couple of weeks ago,
um, I heard some noises

40:15.784 --> 40:17.771
coming from the basement,
like a clanging.

40:17.795 --> 40:19.924
And I asked Betty about it.

40:19.948 --> 40:21.766
She lied right to my face.

40:21.790 --> 40:24.450
What's that about? I don't know.

40:35.504 --> 40:37.014
Now I'm worried.

40:55.524 --> 40:56.764
Julie!

41:03.662 --> 41:04.639
Hi.

41:04.663 --> 41:05.770
Hey.

41:05.794 --> 41:07.772
My, uh, dad found out
about us bowling.

41:07.796 --> 41:09.574
I'm not gonna be able
to do that anytime soon.

41:09.598 --> 41:13.618
Oh. Sorry.

41:13.642 --> 41:15.620
No, no, I'm glad that we did.

41:15.644 --> 41:17.561
I haven't felt like part
of a family in a long time.

41:17.585 --> 41:18.876
Thanks.

41:20.779 --> 41:23.909
I, um, I better get back inside.

41:27.856 --> 41:31.065
The act itself never varies.

41:31.089 --> 41:36.070
But each kiss carries with it
a meaning all its own.

41:36.094 --> 41:41.676
It can convey
a husband's eternal devotion...

41:41.700 --> 41:45.530
Or a wife's enormous regret.

41:49.007 --> 41:53.277
It can symbolize
a mother's growing concern...

41:56.885 --> 42:00.115
Or a lover's growing passion.

42:01.590 --> 42:04.098
But whatever its meaning,

42:04.122 --> 42:08.573
each kiss...

42:08.597 --> 42:11.175
Reflects a basic human need.

42:11.199 --> 42:12.699
Mommy's baby.

42:15.664 --> 42:21.644
The need to connect
to another human being.

42:23.171 --> 42:27.121
This desire is so strong,

42:27.145 --> 42:31.696
it'salways amazing
when some people...

42:31.720 --> 42:33.720
Don't understand it.
